 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#ffffff><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=blame@lighttanksofdaoc>Blame</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://homepages.internet.lu/lordoftherings/images/boromir.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Determined Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 458<br> <font color=#000000>(6/30/03 4:32 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=271.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Please, keep Tendrils as a parry!</span><hr size=1> 1.62 hasn't taken effect in the Uk yet, but I was getting excited about the large growth rate and bleed damage of Dark Tendrils, this and the fact it was being made a mroe damaging alternative to HypDark, off a parry. Evade1 doesn't show at all and I think I have pulled this style off less than 10 times, ever.<br>
<br>
I will never use this style if it goes back to being an evade-reactionary. Please reconsider. We already have a 2-part Evade reactionary chain which is useless. For the time period where mercs had 'Tendrils as a parry reactionary, I heard some good things about this move. I heard nothing good about Orbit or Twin Return, which maybe could use some looking at instead.<br>
<br>
Just my thoguhts. The saracens with their buffbots might argue. A dex/quickness debuff would be nicer to have than a bleed for those of us who have Dual Shadows, but we're hardly going to ever evade an attack in RvR, especialy not an assassins. I'd much prefer a damaging proc, like the 'Zerker, Reaver and Savage all have on some of their styles.<br>
<br>
I don't want to remain with six useless DW styles. Five is enough <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#c0c0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=blame@lighttanksofdaoc>Blame</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://homepages.internet.lu/lordoftherings/images/boromir.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Determined Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 459<br> <font color=#000000>(6/30/03 4:40 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=271.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> edit:</span><hr size=1> Our class still has less parry reactionaries than evade reactionaries anyway. If this takes effect we will have 3 moves that are performable after an evade, Orbit, Twin Return and Dark Tendrils. There is no parry reactionary for Slash or Thrust (and I think Crush as well) , though Thrust has DragonFang as well as a 3-part Evade chain on top of whatever evade-reactionaries DW spec gives us.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#ffffff><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=nirala>Nirala</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>M.C. Hammah</span><br>  Posts: 501<br> <font color=#000000>(6/30/03 6:30 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=271.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: edit:</span><hr size=1> Aye, personally I'd prefer that if they change the effect of Dark Tendrils that it remain a parry reactionary as well.  I'd much rather see our evade chain made more useful. <p>Nirala Kindred<br>
